
[1]embellishment

   EMBEL'LISHMENT, n. The act of adorning.

   1. Ornament; decoration; any thing that adds beauty or elegance; that
   which renders any thing pleasing to the eye, or agreeable to the taste,
   in dress, furniture, manners, or in the fine arts. Rich dresses are
   embellishments of the person. Virtue is an embellishment of the mind,
   and liberal arts, the embellishments of society.
